This article is a statement by President Obama on the death of Nelson Mandela. The President reflects on Mandela's life and accomplishments, describing him as one of the most influential, courageous, and profoundly good human beings. He highlights Mandela's commitment to a democratic and free society and his journey from prisoner to President. The President also acknowledges Mandela's grace, good humor, and ability to acknowledge his own imperfections. He shares how Mandela inspired him personally and expresses gratitude to Mandela's family for sharing him with the world. The President also praises the people of South Africa for their example of renewal, reconciliation, and resilience. He concludes by urging others to forward Mandela's example and strive for a future worthy of his sacrifice.